            <h1 id="fh1">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> What is a Cryptic Hunt?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                Cryptic hunts are online treasure hunts which involve solving brilliant questions either with few hints
                or no hints at all. You are free to surf the internet, even use ChatGPT in any way possible, using
                ciphers, extracting
                metadata or just figuring out the pop culture references.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> What is a Blackbox?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                Blackbox is a logical and analytical approach to finding the arithmetic expression for the given input
                data and that too within provided constraints. You have to form a simple mathematical expression that
                will result in the accurate output that is already given in the question.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> What is the format of the answer for Crypthunt?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                Answers will always be lower-case, alphanumeric and will contain no spaces. Special characters except
                underscore are not allowed. For example, if the answer is "Vitalik Buterin", you would type it in as
                “vitalikbuterin”. (Don't worry, we normalize your inputs anyway).
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> What is the format of the answer for Blackbox?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                Blackbox is a single expression answer type round, so a simple expression is used to answer particular
                questions. The format of the answer shall be a mathematical expression with allowed symbols and variable
                names. For example:-
                The answer type will be “a+b*c”
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> Can we switch the Crypthunt and Blackbox portals in between
                    the game?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                Yes, there is no time constraints to attempt any question. You can attempt any question in between the
                round.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> How much time will be given for each question?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                You will be given a maximum of 3 hrs for the whole game including Crypthunt and Blackbox rounds. Those
                who reach the highest levels by scoring the highest score in the shortest amount of time will be
                declared winners.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> How much time will be given for each question?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                You will be given a maximum of 3 hrs for the whole game.
                The competitors who reach the highest levels in the shortest amount of time will be declared as winners.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> What skills are needed?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                It is not rocket science to solve crypthunt and blackbox questions. Just expertise in problem-solving &
                the art of seeking information will get your job done. Connecting the hints and linking the clues can
                easily help you to reach the correct answer. Blackbox questions can be simply tackled by analyzing the
                input data and the hit-and-trial method to find the expression which satisfies the equation.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> Am I free to search for answers on the internet?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                Yes! The participants are free to use the internet in any way possible to hunt for answers.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> How many questions will there be?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                We won't disclose the numbers but you can expect 10-15 questions.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> What is the duration of the game?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                The game is supposed to continue for 3 hours from 2:00 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. on 28 May 2023.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> Do I need to be a programmer to participate?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                Not at all. While computational thinking will surely help with some questions, there are multiple ways
                to arrive at the solution. We've tried our best to ensure questions are approachable and can be solved
                by non-programming folks.
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class="qdiv">
                <p class="fpara"><b class="plus">&#43</b> Can I share answers/hints with my friends?</p>
            </div>
            <div class="adiv" style="display: none;">
                Team play, answer sharing, hint sharing and collaborating with other competitors, in general, are not
                allowed and any such evidence can lead to disqualification.
            </div>
